sec.p:
In an effort to further characterize the frequency of CSPG4 c.391G > A (p.A131T) in the Netherlands, we performed TaqMan genotyping and Sanger sequencing validation in an independent Dutch cohort of 1219 schizophrenia cases and in the general population-based Rotterdam Study cohort [37] (10,611 subjects). One carrier was identified among the schizophrenia cases (MAFcases 4.1 × 10−4) and three within the general population (MAFpopulation 1.4 × 10−4). The patient carrier had a long history of severe psychiatric illness, including multiple hospital admissions and chronic antipsychotic and antidepressant medication. Her most recent prescriptions included penfluridol oral depot (20 mg/week) and venlafaxine (37.5 mg/day). Family members could not be ascertained for additional psychiatric history or genotyping. Among the three unrelated carriers (maximum pairwise \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
